      <section>
        <title>The Yellen speech</title>
        <chapter>
            <paragraph>On Tuesday, Janet Yellen—the Federal Reserve womanchair—gave a speech that changed the economy assets for many states. She decided
              to continue with the Dovish strategy, during the second meeting.
              She said the Fed still intended to pursue a careful, patient course toward higher interest rates as the economy improved.
              These words caused reactions to other countries, especially about Asia economy.</paragraph>
            </chapter>
        <quote>
          <author>Janet Yellen</author>
          <role>Fed womanchair</role>
          <text>The United States economy remained on track despite a rough start to the year.
            Reflecting global economic and financial developments since December, however,
            the pace of rate increase is now expected to be somewhat slower.</text>
          </quote>
          
